typedef int32_t(* DPM_domainMsgSendResult) (DPM_MCB *ptrDPM, bool isAckNeeded, bool isRelayResult, DPM_Buffer *ptrBuffer, int32_t *errCode)

Description
Domain Specific Message to exchange the buffers from one domain to another.

Parameters
[in]ptrDPMPointer to the DPM MCB
[in]isAckNeededFlag which indicates if the buffers need to be acked or not
[in]isRelayRequestFlag which indicates that the buffers are been relayed in distributed mode and whether the application should be notified via the reporting mechaism
[in]ptrBufferPointer to the DPM buffer
[out]errCodeError code populated on error
Return values
Success- 0
Error- <0

DPM domain

typedef struct DPM_DPCCfg_t DPM_DPCCfg

DPM Processing Chain configuration message.

The structure describes the DPC message. DPC messages are not interpreted by the DPM module. These are simply transported as is to the processing chain. Interpretation of these messages is done by the DPC itself.

typedef struct DPM_HeaderMsg_t DPM_HeaderMsg

DPM Header.

The structure describes the header which is attached to all the messages which are exchanged within the DPM Module.

typedef struct DPM_HWAttribute_t DPM_HWAttribute

DPM HW Attributes.

This the DPM SOC HW Attributes which will allow the module to be ported

typedef struct DPM_MCB_t DPM_MCB

DPM Master control block.

The structure is used to hold all the relevant information required to execute the DPM module

typedef enum DPM_MessageId_e DPM_MessageId

Enumeration for DPM Message Identifiers.

The enumeration describes the message identifers which can be exchanged between the DPM entities.

typedef enum DPM_MessageType_e DPM_MessageType

Message Type enumeration.

The enumeration describes the message types which can be exchanged between the DPM entities.

typedef struct DPM_Msg_t DPM_Msg

DPM Message Format.

The structure describes the DPM message format

Description
Message Handler Function Prototype

Parameters
[in]ptrDPMPointer to the DPM Module

[out]ptrResponseMsgPointer to the response message generated if any
[out]errCodeError code populated by the API
Return values
Success- 0
Error- <0
typedef struct DPM_PipeMsg_t DPM_PipeMsg

DPM Pipe Message.

The structure is used to exchange messages over the DPM Pipe module

typedef struct DPM_Response_t DPM_Response

DPM Response Format.

The structure describes the response. Responses are sent back to the peer which initiated the DPM IPC Request to indicate the status of the operation. Applications are notified though the reporting mechanism

typedef struct DPM_ResultInfo_t DPM_ResultInfo

DPM Result Informational Message.

The DPM result informational messages are exchanged between the peer DPM domains and can be used to pass the DPC results between them.

Enumeration Type Documentation

enum DPM_MessageId_e

Enumeration for DPM Message Identifiers.

The enumeration describes the message identifers which can be exchanged between the DPM entities.

Enumerator
DPM_MessageId_INVALID 

Invalid message identifier:

DPM_MessageId_START 

Message sent to indicate that the DPC has been started.

DPM_MessageId_STOP 

Message sent to indicate that the DPC has been stopped.

DPM_MessageId_DPC_CFG 

DPC configuration command: This is not interpreted by the DPM framework but is passed as is to the processing chain.

DPM_MessageId_BSS_FAULT 

Message sent to indicate that there was a CPU/ESM Fault reported by the BSS.

DPM_MessageId_DPC_ASSERT 

Message sent from the DPC to indicate that an assertion was detected.

DPM_MessageId_RESULT 

Message sent from the DPC to indicate that the results are available.

DPM_MessageId_DPC_INFO 

Message sent from the DPC to indicate that the custom information needs to be reported to the application.

DPM_MessageId_RESPONSE 

Response message.

DPM_MessageId_MAX 

Maximum Message: Nothing beyond this.

enum DPM_MessageType_e

Message Type enumeration.

The enumeration describes the message types which can be exchanged between the DPM entities.

Enumerator
DPM_MessageType_NORMAL 

Normal Message Type:

DPM_MessageType_RELAY 

Relayed Message Type: This is used in the distrubuted domain model when messages are relayed by the DPM from one domain to another.
